<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Oxycheilinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oxycheilinus arenatus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Oxycheilinus arenatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Valenciennes, 1840), commonly known as speckled Maori wrasse, is known from the Red Sea and the Indo-West Pacific: East Africa, Seychelles, Madagascar, and Mascarenes east to Marshall Islands and Samoa, north to Ryukyu Islands (Japan). Generally, from the conservation point of view, they are considered 'Least 
<normalizedToken originalValue="concern’">concern'</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-4.RLTS.T187718A8611549.en" author="Liu, M" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Ocean Science Foundation" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B21" refString="Liu, M, To, A, 2010. Oxycheilinus arenatus, thin-line Maori wrasse. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T187718A8611549. https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-4.RLTS.T187718A8611549.en" title="Oxycheilinus arenatus, thin-line Maori wrasse. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 187718 A 8611549." url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-4.RLTS.T187718A8611549.en" year="2010">Liu and To 2010</bibRefCitation>
). In the Red Sea and Indian Ocean, the species was previously recorded from La 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Réunion">Reunion</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.7339" author="Valenciennes, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Studies (Taipei, Taiwan)" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B30" refString="Valenciennes, A, 1839. [Effectively published Jan. 1840.] Suite du livre seizieme. Labroides. Pp. 1-307. In: Cuvier G, Valenciennes A (Eds) Histoire naturelle des poissons. Tome 14. Levrault, Paris. Pp. i-xxii + 2 pp. + 1-464 + 4 pp., pls. 389-420. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.7339" title="[Effectively published Jan. 1840.] Suite du livre seizieme. Labroides. Pp. 1 - 307. In: Cuvier G, Valenciennes A (Eds) Histoire naturelle des poissons. Tome 14. Levrault, Paris. Pp. i-xxii + 2 pp. + 1 - 464 + 4 pp., pls. 389 - 420." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.7339" year="1839">Valenciennes 1839</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1840" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Cheilinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cheilinus arenatus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Cheilinus arenatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke, R" journalOrPublisher="] Ichthy, Natural History of Fishes of Japan" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B7" refString="Fricke, R, Mulochau, T, Durville, P, Chabanet, P, Tessier, E, Letourneur, Y, 2009. Annotated checklist of the fish species (Pisces) of La Reunion, including a Red List of threatened and declining species. Stuttgarter Beitraege zur Naturkunde A. Neue Serie.2: 1-168." title="Annotated checklist of the fish species (Pisces) of La Reunion, including a Red List of threatened and declining species. Stuttgarter Beitraege zur Naturkunde A. Neue Serie. 2: 1 - 168." year="2009">Fricke et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
), Chagos Archipelago (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.52237" author="Winterbottom, R" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B34" refString="Winterbottom, R, Emery, AR, Holm, E, 1989. An annotated checklist of the fishes of the Chagos Archipelago, central Indian Ocean. Royal Ontario Museum Life Science Contributions, 145: 1-226, pls. 1-8. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.52237" title="An annotated checklist of the fishes of the Chagos Archipelago, central Indian Ocean. Royal Ontario Museum Life Science Contributions, 145: 1 - 226, pls. 1 - 8." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.52237" year="1989">Winterbottom et al. 1989</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1840" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Cheilinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cheilinus arenatus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Cheilinus arenatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Mauritius (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.8809" author="Guenther, ACLG" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Ocean Science Foundation" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B19" refString="Guenther, ACLG, 1862. Catalogue of the fishes in the British Museum. Catalogue of the Acanthopterygii, Pharyngognathi and Anacanthini in the collection of the British Museum. Volume 4. British Museum, London, i-xxi + 1-534. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.8809" title="Catalogue of the fishes in the British Museum. Catalogue of the Acanthopterygii, Pharyngognathi and Anacanthini in the collection of the British Museum. Volume 4. British Museum, London, i-xxi + 1 - 534." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.8809" year="1862">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
1862
</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1840" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Cheilinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cheilinus arenatus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Cheilinus arenatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Seychelles (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, JLB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Studies (Taipei, Taiwan)" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B28" refString="Smith, JLB, Smith, MM, 1963. The fishes of Seychelles. 1st edition. Department of Ichthyology, Rhodes University, Grahamstown, i-viii + 1-215, pls. 1-98." title="The fishes of Seychelles. 1 st edition. Department of Ichthyology, Rhodes University, Grahamstown, i-viii + 1 - 215, pls. 1 - 98." year="1963">Smith and Smith 1963</bibRefCitation>
